UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA LOS ANGELES FOOTBALL MEDIA CONFERENCE
September 23, 2017
Jim Mora
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
UCLA - 34, Stanford - 58   
JIM MORA: It's an incredibly disappointing feeling for all of us.  A lot of things were going right and then all of a sudden it goes wrong.  A dropped pass and a blocked field goal, that was a huge momentum shift.  But that's not an excuse, we should be able to stem the tide.  I still believe great things will happen for us and they will.  I can't remember being around a run defense that gave up so many big plays in my career.  Missed tackles -- when you miss on a good back it's very different.  I'm struggling to understand the targeting.  I was right there for both and they were just football plays.   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT